%div.container-sm.pt-3
  %div.card
    .card-header.text-center
      Quotes
    .card-body.bg-light.border-dark
      %div#carouselQuotations.carousel.slide{"data-ride": "carousel", "data-pause": "hover", "data-interval": "30000"}
        %ol.carousel-indicators.mb-0.bg-secondary
          %li.active{"data-slide-to" => "0", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "1", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "2", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "3", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "4", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "5", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "6", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "7", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "8", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
          %li{"data-slide-to" => "9", "data-target" => "#carouselQuotations"}
        .carousel-inner
          .carousel-item.active
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "Whenever you have money, reputations, power, ego, and complexity in play, it is irrational to assume you are seeing objective science."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                Scott Adams
                %cite{title: "Loserthink"}
                  = link_to "Loserthink", "https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/607083/loserthink-by-scott-adams/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "Individual health is to public health as liberty is to totalitarianism. The moment you depart from treating individuals, and attempt to collectivize a population, you’re not so much an expert as you are an authoritarian control freak disguised as an expert."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                Jordan Schachtel
                %cite{title: "AIER"}
                  = link_to "There Is No Such Thing as a Public Health Expert", "https://www.aier.org/article/there-is-no-such-thing-as-a-public-health-expert/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "Stopping humans from being human will not stop the virus from being a virus!"
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                Roger W. Koops
                %cite{title: "AIER"}
                  = link_to "The Year of Disguises", "https://www.aier.org/article/the-year-of-disguises/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "The idea is that if you are failing to be miserable and sad, you are contributing to the spread of disease and thus prolonging the period of misery for those who are compliant."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                Jeffrey A. Tucker
                %cite{title: "AIER"}
                  = link_to "Massachusetts Bans Dancing Like It’s 1684", "https://www.aier.org/article/massachusetts-bans-dancing-like-its-1684/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "In a saner world, the burden of proof really should belong to the lockdowners, since it is they who overthrew 100 years of public-health wisdom and replaced it with an untested, top-down imposition on freedom and human rights. They never accepted that burden. They took it as axiomatic that a virus could be intimidated and frightened by credentials, edicts, speeches, and masked gendarmes."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                AIER Staff
                %cite{title: "AIER"}
                  = link_to "Lockdowns Do Not Control the Coronavirus: The Evidence", "https://www.aier.org/article/lockdowns-do-not-control-the-coronavirus-the-evidence/"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "Sense is not common anymore during the alleged Covid-19 pandemic. Now you are sick until proven healthy – and contagious by default. The vehicle for this scam is the RT-PCR test run at >35 cycles and beyond. Stop testing and survive."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                Niels Harrit Associate Professor of Chemistry, University of Copenhagen
                %cite{title: "off Guardian"}
                  = link_to "Making something out of nothing: PCR tests, CT values and false positives", "https://off-guardian.org/2021/03/27/making-something-out-of-nothing-pcr-tests-ct-values-and-false-positives/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "Let's focus on the ethical obligation that now runs rampant in our broken societies: everyone’s health is everyone else’s business. Your wants, desires, habits, and routines are mine to police; after all, if we’re not careful, your body could be the source of the next global disease. That means I, or some national or global entity that I control, must be in charge of your life."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                Joakim Book 
                %cite{title: "AIER"}
                  = link_to "Yuval Noah Harari’s Terrifying Pandemic Future", "https://www.aier.org/article/yuval-noah-hararis-terrifying-pandemic-future/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                "Experience has shown that communities faced with epidemics or other adverse events respond best and with the least anxiety when the normal social functioning of the community is least disrupted."
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                D.A Henderson, MD et. al.
                %cite{title: "AIER"}
                  = link_to "How a Free Society Deals with Pandemics", "https://www.aier.org/article/how-a-free-society-deals-with-pandemics-according-to-legendary-epidemiologist-and-smallpox-eradicator-donald-henderson/", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                “The most dangerous man to any government is the man who is able to think things out for himself, without regard to the prevailing superstitions and taboos. Almost inevitably he comes to the conclusion that the government he lives under is dishonest, insane, and intolerable...”
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                H. L. Mencken
                %cite{title: "Prejudices: Third Series"}
                  = link_to "Predjucies: Third Series", "https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/53474", target: "_blank"
          .carousel-item
            %blockquote.blockquote.pb-2
              %p.small
                “We know that no one ever seizes power with the intention of relinquishing it. Power is not a means; it is an end.”
              %footer.blockquote-footer
                George Orwell
                %cite{title: "1984"}
                  = link_to "1984", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nineteen_Eighty-Four", target: "_blank"
